    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, but it sounds pretty heavy. It feels like there's a lot of room for them to dig into my finances if something goes wrong. Are there any specific \"hidden\" risks or things I should be looking for in the wording that might make this clause even more dangerous for me?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are right to be cautious; this clause is quite broad, which is where the danger lies. Look closely at the phrase \"arising out of or occurring in connection with.\" This language is very wide and could potentially cover things that are tangentially related to your work, not just direct breaches. Also, check if the clause specifies *only* your negligence, or if it covers the Client's own actions as well. If it's too broad, it could force you to cover things that are not your fault.",
      "source": "target",
